This paper discusses the benefits of artificial intelligence technologies in crisis response, which is a topic that falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper specifically mentions the use of robotics (cs.RO), ontology and semantic web (cs.AI), and multi-agent systems (cs.CR) in crisis response. Additionally, the paper discusses the management of resources, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
